This paper deals with the problem of inferring the position and properties of lanes on urban roads using LiDAR remission grid maps and deep neural networks. This problem involves computer vision (CV) techniques for segmentation and robotics (RO) for autonomous car operation. The use of deep neural networks (DNN) for segmentation also suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of road maps using codes, which could involve natural language processing (CL) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
